article_title: British Parliament Approves Airstrikes in Iraq Against Islamic State
article_text:
LONDON—British Prime Minister David Cameron on Friday secured parliamentary support for the U.K. to join U.S.-led airstrikes against the militant groupIslamic State, the final political hurdle before launching military action.

In a special parliamentary session Friday, 524 lawmakers voted in favor of participating in airstrikes in Iraq against the militant group known as Islamic State, and 43 voted against.
